---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="BeaconGuard Assurance | AI Policy Control and Evidence Boundary"
  description="BeaconGuard provides inline deterministic authorization and evidence capture before AI execution in high-risk enterprise workflows across healthcare, financial services, and regulated internal automation."
>
  <section class="landing">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">Inline Runtime Control Boundary</p>
    <h1>Policy control before AI execution. Evidence after every decision.</h1>
    <p class="hero-subheadline">
      BeaconGuard is an inline deterministic authorization and evidence boundary for high-risk enterprise AI workflows across healthcare, financial services, and regulated internal automation.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-subheadline">
      BeaconGuard deploys alongside existing enterprise applications as an inline policy proxy. It evaluates signed request metadata, workflow context, user role, source-system trust, approved-pathway status, freshness controls, and governed policy before model execution. It returns allow, deny, or needs-review decisions and preserves audit-ready evidence.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/platform">Review the Platform</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/healthcare">Healthcare Architecture Review</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/fintech">Financial Workflow Review</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Existing Systems Remain in Place</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard does not replace existing enterprise applications. It interposes an inline policy enforcement boundary at the AI request layer so existing workflows can be made fail-closed, policy-controlled, and auditable before model execution.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Existing applications continue to own workflow logic and systems of record.</li>
      <li>BeaconGuard enforces policy before AI or model execution.</li>
      <li>Decision evidence is preserved for security, privacy, compliance, risk, and audit review.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>Review Paths</h2>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--compact">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Healthcare Operations</h3>
        <p>For PHI-sensitive operational workflows, approved AI pathways, privacy review routing, role-based request controls, and audit-ready decision evidence.</p>
        <p><a href="/healthcare">Review Healthcare Use Case</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Financial Workflows</h3>
        <p>For AML, KYC, fraud, dispute review, customer-impacting recommendations, and analyst-assist workflows requiring deterministic request control before model execution.</p>
        <p><a href="/fintech">Review Financial Use Case</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Regulated Internal Automation</h3>
        <p>For internal AI agents or automations that need policy enforcement before acting against production systems or sensitive operational data.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <h2>What BeaconGuard Controls</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard evaluates deterministic context tags, approved-pathway status, source-system metadata, signed request attributes, and governed policy before model execution.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Which AI requests are allowed to proceed</li>
      <li>Which requests are denied before model execution</li>
      <li>Which requests require human review</li>
      <li>Which model pathways are approved for the workflow</li>
      <li>Which user roles may invoke the workflow</li>
      <li>Which signed context tags and source-system attributes are required</li>
      <li>Which evidence is preserved for later review</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section homepage-block">
    <p class="section-label">Control boundary overview</p>
    <h2>Inline Policy Proxy at the AI Request Boundary</h2>
    <div class="infra-diagram home-boundary-diagram">
      <div class="flow-diagram flow-diagram--stack home-request-flow">
        <div class="flow-step flow-node-primary">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Existing Enterprise Application</p>
          <p>Owns workflow logic, records, user experience, and operational process.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
        <div class="flow-step flow-node-boundary">
          <p class="flow-step-title">BeaconGuard Policy Enforcement Point</p>
          <p>Evaluates signed request metadata, source-system trust, context tags, freshness windows, and governed policy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
        <div class="flow-step flow-node-evidence">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Approved Model Endpoint</p>
          <p>Receives only allowed requests after execution-boundary authorization.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-diagram flow-branch home-review-branch">
        <p class="flow-branch-title">Evidence &amp; review stream</p>
        <div class="flow-step flow-node-evidence flow-pulse">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Audit-Ready Evidence</p>
          <p>Allow, deny, and needs-review decisions preserve policy inputs and decision context.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="flow-path-note">
      BeaconGuard is the fail-closed checkpoint before model execution, not a replacement for the systems that already run the business workflow.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .home-boundary-section,
    .homepage-block {
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .home-request-flow,
      .home-review-branch {
        display: block;
        gap: 0;
      }

      .home-request-flow .flow-step {
        width: 100%;
        min-height: 0;
      }

      .home-request-flow .flow-arrow {
        display: none;
      }

      .home-request-flow .flow-step + .flow-step {
        margin-top: 1rem;
        position: relative;
        padding-top: 1.1rem;
      }

      .home-request-flow .flow-step + .flow-step::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        left: 1rem;
        top: 0;
        width: 2px;
        height: 0.9rem;
        background: var(--brand-accent);
        transform: translateY(-65%);
      }

      .home-request-flow .flow-step + .flow-step::after {
        content: "↓";
        position: absolute;
        left: 1rem;
        top: 0;
        transform: translate(-45%, -100%);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1;
        color: var(--brand-accent);
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
